==English==
===Etymology===
From Old French ''encrochier''

===Verb===
'''encroach'''
#''(intransitive)'' [[Intrude]] unrightfully on someone else's rights or territory.
#''(intransitive)'' Advance gradually beyond [[due]] limits.

